-- Acciona, FCC May Bid for Madrid Water Firm Stake, Expansion Says
-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-03-14T06:48:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/acciona-fcc-may-bid-for-madrid-water-firm-stake-expansion-says.html
Acciona SA (ANA) ,  Sociedad General de
Aguas de Barcelona SA  and  Fomento de Construcciones y Contratas
SA  may separately bid for a stake in  Madrid ’s water company,
 Expansion  said, citing unidentified people familiar with the
matter.  The Spanish companies may team up with foreign investors to
buy between 25 and 25 percent of Canal de Isabel II, as the
water company is known, Expansion said.  Banco Bilbao Vizcaya
Argentaria SA (BBVA)  is Canal’s adviser, Expansion said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
 eduarterubia@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emma Ross-Thomas in Madrid at 
 erossthomas@bloomberg.net  